commit 89dfd146fc6f1161f14d62c728cf8c2a4f2ba94e
Author: Matthias Meusburger <matthias.meusburger@biblibre.com>
Date:   Mon Feb 13 16:35:05 2023 +0100

    MT39895: Add throttle to overtime edits
    
    In some cases (network hiccups for example), the POST request for editing an
    overtime can be sent twice.
    
    This patch adds a minimum delay between two edits of a given overtime of 1
    second by default.
    
    This value can be overridden with the following setting in custom_options.php:
    
    $config['post_requests_throttle'] = n;
    
    Test plan:
    
    1) Set post_requests_throttle to a large enough value in custom_options.php
       (20 seconds should be enough)
    
    2) Edit an overtime, check that the modification is made.
    
    3) Within the 20 seconds, edit this overtime again, check that the modification
       is denied, with a message telling you to wait a few seconds before trying
       again.
    
    4) After the 20 seconds are expired, edit this overtime again, and check that
       the modification is made.
--> Traité autrement sur 24.04.xx

